XML can be validated in two ways--1.against DTD(Document Type Definition),2.against XSD(XML Schema Definition)
XML -- eXtensible Markup Language. it is designed to store and transport data,XML is designed to carry data not to display data.
XML is self-descriptive which means it describes both content and structure. XMl is platform independent and language independent.
Differences with HTML: 1. HTML is used to display data and the looks whereas XML is used to transport and store data.2. HTML is markup
language whereas XML is framework for that. 3. HTML is not case sensitive whereas XML is case sensitive.4. HTML has its own predefined 
tags whereas XML we can design tags as per need. 5. HTML is static whereas XML is dynamic 6. HTML does not preserve whitespace whereas
XMl preserves whitespace.
